Class SingleList<T extends Comparable<T>>

java.lang.Object
cp213.SingleLink<T>
cp213.SingleList<T>
Type Parameters:
T - this SingleList data type.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<T>
public class SingleList<T extends Comparable<T>> extends SingleLink<T>
A single linked list structure of Node T objects. These data objects must be Comparable - i.e. they must provide the compareTo method. Only the T object contained in the priority queue is visible through the standard priority queue methods. Extends the SingleLink class.
Version:
2024-09-01
Author:
David Brown

    • split

      public void split(SingleList<T> left, SingleList<T> right)
      Splits the contents of this SingleList into the left and right SingleLists. Moves nodes only - does not move object or call the high-level methods insert or remove. this SingleList is empty when done. The first half of this SingleList is moved to left, and the last half of this SingleList is moved to right. If the resulting lengths are not the same, left should have one more object than right. Order is preserved.
      Parameters:
      left - The first SingleList to move nodes to.
      right - The second SingleList to move nodes to.

    • splitAlternate

      public void splitAlternate(SingleList<T> left, SingleList<T> right)
      Splits the contents of this SingleList into the left and right SingleLists. Moves nodes only - does not move object or call the high-level methods insert or remove. this SingleList is empty when done. Nodes are moved alternately from this SingleList to left and right. Order is preserved.
      Parameters:
      left - The first SingleList to move nodes to.
      right - The second SingleList to move nodes to.

    • union

      public void union(SingleList<T> left, SingleList<T> right)

      Parameters:
      left - The first SingleList to create a union from.
